"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"FAUNA:6.11\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">6.11</span> 标题：蝎子（scorpion）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：עַקְרָב</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：‘aqrav)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:4\">NUM 34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:15\">DEU 8:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:3\">JOS 15:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:36\">JDG 1:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:11\">1KI 12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:14\">1KI 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:11\">2CH 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:14\">2CH 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:6\">EZK 2:6</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：σκορπίος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：scorpios)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:19\">LUK 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:12\">LUK 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude9:3\">REV 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude9:5\">REV 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude9:10\">REV 9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis26:7\">SIR 26:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis39:30\">SIR 39:30</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">讨论</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p><figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0793_scorpion.jpg\" alt=\"WEB-0793_scorpion\"></figure>学者一致同意这些词是指蝎子。许多学者认为，<em>‘aqrav</em> 也是一种用来惩罚罪犯的鞭子的别称。</p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>蝎子是一种八足动物。在以色列地，蝎子的体长大约为13厘米（5英寸），但在一些热带国家，长度可达18厘米（7英寸）。蝎子的第一对足有螯，与螃蟹相似；尾巴可以拱起弯到头部上方，上面长着毒刺。蝎子以其他的昆虫和小型爬虫为食，例如小蜥蜴。蝎子用螯抓住猎物，并用尾巴螫刺，这样能杀死猎物，或者使其麻痹。</p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">特殊意义或象征意义</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>在《希伯来圣经》中，蝎子代表着恶劣、不适合居住的生活环境。</p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>《列王纪上》和《历代志下》经文中出现的&quot;蝎子&quot;一词，很可能是指一种打人特别痛的鞭子，因此<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New English Bible (1970)\">NEB</abbr> 将这个词译为&quot;lash&quot;（&quot;鞭子&quot;），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Jerusalem Bible (1966)\">JB</abbr> 译为&quot;loaded scourge&quot;（&quot;重重的鞭打&quot;），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Today&#x27;s English Version (Good News Bible)\">TEV</abbr> 译为&quot;bullwhips&quot;（&quot;赶牛鞭&quot;）。许多非英文译本译为&quot;蝎子鞭&quot;之类的短语。</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:4\">NUM 34:4</a> 、<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:3\">JOS 15:3</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:36\">JDG 1:36</a> 提到一个名为<em>ma‘aleh ‘aqrabim</em> （意为&quot;蝎子通道&quot;）的地方，但因为在翻译地名时通常不将字义翻译出来，因此通常译成&quot;亚克拉滨斜坡&quot;。</p>\n<p>除了北极苔原和一些岛屿之外，蝎子几乎遍布全球，因此在大多数地方，都可以找到对等的译词。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
